    "# Paul Florio Idea 1\n",
    "## Early Education Impacts on Future Economic Success\n",
    "\n",
    "My first idea is centered around the impact of how a decision early on in a person's life of attending early education systems can impact their potential economic impacts when they reach the workforce. From there, by using the results of the models, I hope to be able to explain some discrepancies that appear and how to solve them.\n",
    "\n",
    "I plan to get the data for this project from a couple of sources. One of the more well-known sources for this project would simply be using the US census data since it is available to the public and does deep categorizations of demographics within the data. The specific source I am using with the the census would be a survey called the \"American Community Survey\". Another great source that I will be using is from the National Center for Educational Statistics (NCES) which provides a broad range of data regarding education in the US. The specific data I would use would come from the Early Childhood Longitudinal Study (ECLS) which is a program that collects important information about childrenâ€™s knowledge, skills, and educational experiences. I may find other sources as needed as I move along with the project but these are the main two I have identified for now.\n",
    "\n",
    "https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/acs/data.html\n",
    "https://nces.ed.gov/ecls/dataproducts.asp#K-5\n",
